@node "Intro" "Introduction..."
@next "What Are These Things"



   This archive contains backdrop iff pictures (tiles) for use with NewIcons.
Actually, you could use them whether or not you use NewIcons, but if you do,
you will already be using the NewIcons base palette, so why not give @{"NewIcons" link "Credit" 0}
a try?

@endnode

@node "How Do I Use These Things..." "How The Hell Do I Use These Things..."
@next "Blame"



    How To Use These Backdrops:



    WB 3.x

       Launch the WBPattern Tool in the Preferences directory. C'mon now,
       it was easy enough for C= to write, can it really be that difficult
       to operate?


    WB 2.x

       Immediately locate the application @{"WBPicture" link "More Credit" 0}. Place this in your
       Preferences directory. I can only assume that Nicola figured that the
       monkeys at C= would someday try to use the application, so he made it
       simple enough for even them to use.


    WB 1.x

       a) Upgrade to WB 2.x. Then follow the instructions above.
       b) Upgrade to WB 3.x. Then follow the instructions above above.

@endnode

